reviews.text: Such an awesome little shop. The showroom is excellent but the workshop in the back is where the real magic happens! They are fantastic artists that transform simple gourds into usable household decor. As soon as our master bedroom is completed I'll be back to purchase 2 lamps for our nightstands

So fun! I came here to make a nightlight, and Graham was so friendly, enthusiastic, and helpful! The art she makes is beautiful, and the gourds make for a surprisingly robust medium! This was fun little adventure, and I'd recommend it to anybody looking for something unusual and unique!

What a fun place! 
You can have a short visit just to buy some gourds or gourds art, walk in the gourds tunnel, make a tiny gourds necklace or have a workshop. 

The owner is a wonderful, open, funny and welcoming lady, who is very artistic. The studio is amazing, cozy and full with beautiful gourds.
We enjoyed our visit very much and will be back!

Don't forget to take a walk in the Eco Village later.

The make your own gourd art package is a wonderful way to spend part of an afternoon that begins with some Gourd  Education, continues with power tool usage, and ends with a fantastic memento. Great artist, great person, great experience through and through.

This is a must-see destination if you like art, are interested in sustainability, and just want to visit a cool place. Located add Ecco Village in Ithaca this is a gallery and workplace of an amazing artist who Fashions pieces from gourds that have been dried. The building itself is very impressive and fashioned from beautiful wood. The gourds are grown on site which makes the whole experience.

I hosted a corporate team retreat at Argos Inn and Argos Warehouse event space. 9 of us enjoyed wonderful rooms, relaxing at the bar in the evenings, and pleasant breakfasts in the sunroom. Our business meetings in the conference room and Lounge were more creative and productive for the hip-comfortable atmosphere and attentive service by Argos staff. Beats a chain hotel experience hands-down. Highly recommend for a business meeting!

I hosted a business associate and they had an exceptional stay at the Argos. Beautiful throughout, attentive and friendly staff, great coffee every morning along with breakfast, and terrific music (but not too late) several nights each week. Highly recommended.
This newly renovated Inn has tons of charm, a great bar and seating areas inside and out. Outdoors offers two separate sections with occasionl musical acts performing.

What a gem. Beautiful old house converted into a bed & breakfast. Designed to marry antiques and modern art - strikes the balance of historic and cool. The bar has a deep selection of whisky, mezcal, and gin - cocktails will give NYC bars a run for their money. Worth a trip whether you’re coming from the city or are just in the neighborhood.

Really cool atmosphere. An old house renovated into this unique and cozy bar. They advertise seating for 80 and a dance floor for 130. There is an entire second floor that we didn't check out but the first floor has lots of parlor-style seating and a large sunroom with three giant tables with bench seating. The whole place has this eclectic Victorian vibe. Our bartender was really cool and we just had a very nice time.

Our family stopped here while camping in the area. It was a beautiful fall day, and this place was BUSY. We ordered flights, and waited over an hour for a table for dinner. It was DEFINITELY worth the wait. We enjoyed tasting our flights outside on a picnic table. By the time we talked, enjoyed the music and finished our beers, we were seated for dinner. The soups were fantastic, and the pizzas were delicious. We wanted to especially thank our server, Valerie, as she was one of the best servers we have encountered.  Only one negative thing to mention was the host who took our name - he was obviously having a bad day and had a bad attitude. We were impressed enough to purchase a shirt, and beers to take back to the campsite. We greatly enjoyed our evening at Ithaca Beer Co.

This is one of my favorite breweries, definitely try the fan favorite flower power IPA, otherwise there are a number of local beers that you can only get direct from the brewery or within a 15 to 20 mile radius of the brewery.

The food is really good as well. I recommend the beer cheese soup, seasonal salad and the sandwiches. We make this a regular stop when we go to Ithaca.
Pay for the tour. A great tour guide and personalized tour was given. We learned a lot about the beers and facility. Thanks!
Great beer.  Pizza was very good.  Atmosphere and service was top notch.  Hope to return in the summer to sit outside.

It’s a great place to hangout in the summer. There is a big patio outside to sit and have food. They also have a restaurant inside but, very busy. So, it might be good to make a reservation if they accept the same.

The food was phenomenal. Our server Mary was very pleasant and attentive. Great place to eat and the atmosphere is so nice. Highly recommend. 😁 Will be returning. The burger and , the butternut squash and sweet potato soup was awesome. place is just delish. 🎯👍👍👍

The daily specials were very good, especially the beet salad, which was delicious.  I enjoyed the chicken soup - tasty with just a hint of tanginess.  Good for a cold evening.  We had the Ultimate margarita.  It's not a large cocktail as margaritas sometimes are, but was of very good quality. The staff were all friendly with attentive and prompt service. I would definitely eat here again.
Excellent fusion restaurant. Started with guacamole with pistachios which was amazing. Had some excellent drinks and a delicious flat bread pizza

If you are a foodie or love exploring interesting favor experiences, this place is for you. I had bites of the brussel sprouts appetizer, the sweet potato appetizer, the black bean burger, and the cauliflower steak, and MY GOD, absolutely amazing all around. Complicated evolving flavor palettes and fantastic creativity, this place is worth experiencing.
Agava is one of the best places relative to what is around. It's pricy. But the quality is high and service is good. The food is also delicious
Cozy ambience, convivial bar, attentive and friendly service. Best shrimp and grits.The bread pudding was dreamy. I look forward to working my way through the creative cocktail list.
Great battered fish and shrimp and the cole slaw is amazing. Quick and friendly service.  Would recommend to others to try out. Inside and outside seating as well to enjoy your meal. 😊

Delicious food, fun and friendly atmosphere! If you find yourself in Ithaca, this place is  definitely a must stop for food. The fresh raw oysters are a must try seafood lovers and their vegetarian dishes are exceptionl. If Creole style meals are your thing then you definitely want to check this place out!

My wife and I visited the restaurant last night in celebration of our anniversary.  We sat at the bar and had a fantastic time! Our bartenders, Caleb and Bobby were awesome. Both were personable and efficient.  We had some happy hour food, raw oysters, crab cakes, and fish tacos.  Everything was delicious.  Caleb even made my wife a specialty cocktail which was out of this world. Although we don't get the chance to come to this restaurant as often as we like, we are never disappointed.  Thank you so much for maintaining a high standard for food and service. We'll definitely be back ASAP.
Incredible. Food and customer service were both outstanding. Jonathon and the whole FOH were great. The Trainer was doing a good job too.  Compliments to the chef and the entire BOH.
The food was really good. I got the grilled cheese sandwich with veggies and bacon, it was fantastic.

This used to be one of my favorite restaurants and I always recommended it to visitors for brunch. My last few visits have been disappointing. The wait staff is always wonderful, but the quality of the food is declining. Yesterday I ordered chicken and waffles, and what I received was one small waffle and three chicken wings. The wings were absolutely coated in paprika but had no other seasoning--they were somehow over-seasoned and underseasoned at the same time. They were rubbery and didn't go well with the waffle at all. For $15, this was terrible. Overall, the portions seem to be shrinking and the quality isn't what it used to be. I won't be returning unless there's a serious improvement in the food standards.

While visiting Ithaca for a music festival, we happened upon this place accidentally while looking for parking. We decided to get brunch here the next morning! It has a cozy local vibe, mixed with a contemporary and rustic touches. The food was outstanding and they serve food primarily sourced from the area. The menu was concise. Overall great find!!!!

Intimate and fun atmosphere with a plentiful selection of beer, wine and spirits - including a outdoor space in the warmer months. Staff has always been pleasant, but some of the prices are somewhat steep for the portion size ($13 for a breakfast sandwich).
Waitress was friendly, food was alright. Pokestop in range.

result.name: The Heights Restaurant and H Bar

reviews.text: I have never expected such a delicious dinner at Ithaca. Absolutely you should visit the restaurant. The meat are well cooked and soft, tasting like cloud. The chief was so specialized at mixing different food together but keeping the taste like a symphony. Just mention an example, the grilled octopus was side with a grape. But they matched each other. Magical.

The meal was amazing. Large portion size and presentation make it even more elegant. The location has a great meeting room that supports a smaller group but comfortably. The  staff were very attentive. Great place, cannot wait to go again.
The last great restaurant in Ithaca. Great wine and beer list.  Excellent starters and nice house salad.  Salmon and steak both excellent. Service very prompt and attentive.

Great spot in Ithaca for a dinner with friends or family. The chef was extremely accommodating for the group in terms of allergies, gluten-free, etc. Brought out a lot of options. Everything tasted delicious and service was top-notch. Create separate private rooms for large groups, so the atmosphere was great. Highly recommend!
Excellent food, nice variety and professional service. A great place to go for a specialized occasion.
Always great service, delicious food, and you can't beat the atmosphere! The special cocktail was exceptional.
Comfortable updated decor. Good service. Great food!
Very nice, upscale atmosphere. Great for a group of your friends or dining alone. Has many delicious menu options for all sorts of cravings, little and big.
Good meal in a very nice setting. I thought the menu was a little bit thin, would have liked a few more entrees to choose from. The clam chowder deserves to be award winning.

The food was absolutely amazing. Every member of our party loved their entree, but we had to remind our waitress multiple times about appetizers we had ordered. Some didn’t get delivered despite asking a few times.. that’s our only complaint!
Both chocolate lava and deep fried potato wedges with chipotle sauce were superb! The service is also pleasant. Be prepared to wait to be seated if you come here during dinner time though.

Went with friends who knew the menu so they ordered, would definitely ask for recommendations from the waiter if you’re new to it! Food is always amazing, and flavorful, although it’s a bit pricey it’s worth it to split with friends and share dishes- each one is packed with so much flavor it’s truly the tapas experience 👌 It’s a bit packed but the patios open during the summer and I’d recommended making a reservation if you have more than 3 people otherwise the wait can be long. The bread pudding and coconut ice cream was a spiritual experience would def recommend to everyone!

Just a Taste has long been my favorite restaurant in town.  Some dishes are always on the menu, some rotate in and out, occasionally one is just ok, but generally the food is great.  The wait staff is outstanding - they're very cool.  The wine selection is large and quite good, the patio is pleasant, and it's chill.  Go eat there.
Always a delightful experience. The food is always on point. The wait staff members are always helpful and accommodating.
Great selection of small dishes. Good place to go with a group. Would recommend the wine sampler options.

Service was a bit rude. We felt like we were being rushed out and not appreciated even though the restaurant was mostly empty. Food tasted okay excepted for the overly burnt riblets, which they replaced.

Got a love the perfect Margarita's. And the food is good too lol.  😊
this is the 3 course meal deal ! Excellent! Less than $13.00.

Terrible!  We waited 45 mins for our appetizers, and they brought them out with the entrees.  Drinks showed up one at a time, with a simple soda coming last.  Food was warm to cold.  2 dirty plates that we asked for replacements...and never got.  Yelling from the kitchen.  Nobody seemed to be clicking in there.  I thank the manager for knocking some prices off our check, but we won't be going to this one again.  Oh, and it wasn't even crowded. Ugh.
Service was very quick. Food came out quickly and all at the right temperature. Jenna was the waitress and she checked in promptly and kept up on drinks. Nice quick dinner with my family.
Food not cooked well. Asked for well done burger and it was pink in the middle. Steak, asked for medium, was very very rare. Waitstaff was very nice, but will not be going back.

There was a time Ithaca had a German bakery, deli, and other yummy Euro luxuries.  Here you can still buy great coffee, coffee related products, Austrian chocolates,  marzipan pigs, as well as great local sweets, beers, olive oils and cheeses from here and all over.  The gift baskets are sweet, the staff friendly, and I can't resist stopping weekly to see what's new.  My personal favs: the cheeses, hot chocolate choices, and anything on the back wall.

Great service with friendly staff members always knowledge about the store's offerings. Lots of in-store blends of coffee and tea with big windows at the front of the store and a small seating area to enjoy some pastries 🥐!

Food and coffe are excellent but services should improved. I asked for reward program, staff gave me the card without explaining that my order didn't added in the program, yet. When I checked my ORDER HISTORY and found out that it wrote..You haven't placed any orders yet. That made me very upset.

Absolutely loved this shop.  The variety of items in there made me giddy.  We were traveling and just wanted to pick up a cup of coffee.  I was surprised to find not only coffee and sandwiches but the selection of meats/cheeses, chocolates, wine, and beer made me think I was at a Toy R Us for adults.
Triphammer Tavern & Coffee Staff are terrific! Welcoming, friendly, kind
Loving coming here. Great coffee , better vibe and the coolest baristas
Staff is SO HELPFUL and friendly, always locating JUST what I am looking for. Thank you wonderful gals!
Helpful and knowledgeable staff made the sale a pleasurable conversation

Every Friday for urs I went they to get educated in  wines.in fall they offer ciders at fading.Xmas season they offer whiskeys wine tastings are good I teach you about The Vineyards The Grapes the different tastes you can learn and appreciate it and be a kind of sore by the end of the wine tasting and they give you good discounts just a nice variety store
Great selection and friendly service many Fridays and Saturdays have wine tastings.

Great burgers, great wings, and cold beer. What more can you ask for? Salads are really good if you're into that. Last time I went I had the Old Bay chicken sandwich and it was really good. Definitely recommend.

Ithaca Ale House is one of many unique dining experiences in the beautiful city of Ithaca, N.Y.!

So many selections to choose from, this pub-like restaurant makes you feel like you are eating/drinking in a real English pub!!

Reasonably priced, attentive staff, pleasant atmosphere!
Highly recommended!!
I went specifically for the burger of the week (I am friends with Mike Brindisi. The burger is named after his newborn son). I was not disappointed. You really can't go wrong with smoked gouda. 👍🏾👍🏾
The grilled cheese was highly recommended and absolutely delivered. Great beer selection on tap. Friendly staff. If I am back in Ithaca, I would definitely come back here!
The service was good and our waitress was friendly.  The portions were huge and the burger was great.  I'd recommend giving this place a try!

Usually not an issue but the last time here, service was extremely slow.  Almost 30 minutes passed from the time we were seated until someone came to ask us if anyone was even helping us.  The place was far from being busy.  

Food was good though.  Price was decent.  We'll be back.
We went there for my birthday dinner.

Had the cheese curd bacon burger today.  In my opinion, one of the best burgers I've ever eaten. Juicy, large, delicious.  Great sampler platter too.  Not to mention the boneless wings were second to none.  Definitely going back
The staff is so overworked and harrased. The amount of disrespect to employees is insane and the place is ran completely incompetently.
Staff was super friendly, but service was a bit slow. Still....wings!

The ambience was nice, calamari was delicious, clams fresh, the chicken parm was a bit funky. Would have sent it back but since it was the last meal of the night I decided it best to leave it be. Overall, I would give it another shot but would recommend going earlier in the night.

Spending Christmas week in Ithaca with my gf and had stopped in for dinner two days before Christmas. Kind of has a parlor/boutique appeal as the bar(kinda a twist between Irish Pub and Gaslamp style) as the central focal point in the restaurant. Ordered the two specials that evening and it was delicious. I can’t say enough about the quality of presentation and taste of our food. Polished our meal off with a tasty Cab Sav and our server(Emily) was incredible. I highly recommend this as a stop for any foodie staying in the Finger Lake region.
My girlfriend and I went here yesterday and had a great meal. Our server, Emily was very pleasant and attentive and the food was fantastic. We highly recommend!

Came here for lunch, and the food, atmosphere, and service was great! The calamari and the specialty orders here are fantastic (especially the sweet potato fries that came with the burger!), but the pasta isn't anything special and a little overpriced. Would still recommend if you are looking for a grill in the Commons area.
Great atmosphere and the food is great. Try the shrimp scampi

Completely delicious. Ordered delivery and it was earlier than expected, the food was hot and the chicken wings are huge! My husband and I can't wait to try everything on the menu! Best delivery in Ithaca so far.
Good food very friendly staff. Had it at the restaurant and for delivery. Both times it has been good. Give it a try!

The service is horrible. I ordered food for delivery and they didn't ask for my card information so I assumed I could give them my card when they got here or they already had my card information (already ordered from here) and once the delivery driver got here he told me he could take my card so I said I could run up to my room to get cash but he said he had to go. DONT GO HERE. bad customer service.

Won’t come back again after this time because of the unfriendly service and awful food. The chicken wings are extremely salty the first time I tried them. This time they are even more salty, and also bloody, even if I noted well done. The chicken wings I ordered this time are extremely intolerable. And the service is disappointing. The staffs kept chatting for a long time and kept me waiting. She finally noticed me after I said hi for several times, and then kept me waiting for a while.

Minus 2 stars, because when I got there I was told my burger would be ready in 5 minutes, but I had to wait for more than 20.
Plus one star because the staff was really friendly. Apparently my order took longer than expected because they had to prepare the local beef.
Minus one star because they forgot the fried onions :/
Plus one star because I want to end up with 4 stars anyway. I liked the burger and especially the garlic fries, and I would go there again.
In conclusion, if you want to go for the local beef, it might take a bit longer.

result.name: Sacred Root Kava Lounge & Tea Bar

reviews.text: Great tea selection in this hidden gem of a lounge with musicians scheduled all week. Whether you hang out trying new teas or grab a lounge chair or sofa to chill, there will  be plenty of spots to explore.

The drink tastes very special. To me, it mixed the environment of East and atmosphere of West vey well. There aren’t many people at night, so you can have a very great time with your friends. Just few of you can have a nice deep talk. Or a group of you can have a party in a special room.

Great atmosphere. Definitely encapsulates the Ithaca Earthy vibe. Alcohol free place to spend an evening. Music is always at the forefront. Check the listings to make sure it's music you may like. There's such a variety it may not be your favorite type. Staff was very friendly and very knowledgeable about Kava which is an interesting experience unto itself. Definitely worth checking out for something different on a night out.
An amazing place with tons of atmosphere. Everyone you meet WILL be friendly and helpful. Ask questions, get answers. This is a go-to spot to visit when you hit Ithaca.

I love this place! It has great atmosphere, music, art, special events, a dance floor, Kava in flavors and great organic teas and tasty treats. The owners are awesome and the staff is always friendly. I highly recommend a visit, especially if you enjoy eclectic, artsy places with a cozy atmosphere.

Had a super fun time here while visiting my family in Ithaca! They have good music and it was decently crowded without getting too hot or to the point where it took too long to get a drink. The bartenders are on top of their game, only issue is the bar seems a little under stocked but the drinks that they do have are pretty good and pretty strong. Also if you go up on the stages to dance make sure you have good footing because they do get drinks spilled on them and get a little slippery (coming from someone who has a big bruise right now lol). Also there’s a very cute security guard so if you’re seeing this hit me up haha
Lot of fun. The place is ALIVE on the weekends. Also Trivia Tuesdays are a great time!
The dj doesn’t take requests and plays exclusively trap music that no one knows. This place would be so much more fun with an early 2000s mix or more well known songs

I’m not the right person to review this place. I have a love for a certain kind of night club and this really isn’t it. But if you’re looking for pop music and a very lively party with collage kids this is it.
Please clean the floors they were sticky early Friday night it was rather unpleasant.

Excellent service, friendly atmosphere, lot of seating space. Bunch of board games to play. 

Not a lot of food options, that’s why they allow you to bring outside food.

Lot of beer options, try local, you can’t go wrong with any of the options on the board, however bartender will help you in narrowing down the choices.
Solid beers. Recommend the liquid crush ipa and the running with scissors dipa.

Breweries are usually cool spots to hang but the beer is not always tops. Liquid State is cool, with great service and exceptional beer. Some of the best tasting beers I’ve ever had. And I’ve had a lot. Great find!

Beers are OK - they have their own beers as well as some from other breweries. Flights available. They don't have a full menu but have some snacks available - soft pretzels are really good.
Atmosphere is pretty good, seating is picnic table style so is a good place for larger groups, although it gets pretty loud when it is crowded.
Skee Ball is cool, only $0.25! 
Parking available both in front and behind the building.

Certainly a much needed new spot in Ithaca. Great place for hanging with friends and playing games. However they still need to work on their beer.
The sonic is decent, but I found the Liquid crush to be flat and the Local Vibe to lack flavor

Poutine burger was unique and great! Went on a weekday and it was dead but seems like they do a lot of delivery orders for campus. Also, has a walkthrough to the bar next door. Would recommend for some great, casual dining.

This review is for their food truck, which should be more like a 3.5.  The food was hot, fresh, and decently portioned.  Their gouda mac and cheese could have used more of a kick, but the sauce for their fries was quite good.  Pretty pricey, though, at least at the food truck.  The mac and cheese should have been more like $8 or $9 for a full serving, not $13.  Fries were a fairly high $6.  Not the worst, but a bit high for how the food tasted.  Otherwise, they operate a fairly high-quality food truck.  I got my food pretty quickly, too.  Be aware, however, that their food truck menu is limited compared to their full service menu.

Luna is one of my absolute favorite places to eat in Ithaca!  No matter what the situation, Luna seems like the perfect option, no matter who I’m dining with and what their preferences are. Luna offers great options for me, as a gluten free person and I enjoy trying their new dishes. I love the atmosphere and am always helped by friendly staff. I feel so lucky to have Luna in the neighborhood and love supporting this local gem!

DONT GO HERE. They have the saltiestttt food. I have been there twice, once for tacos and the pork taco was so salty I could not eat it. Recently went again and got the mahi sandwich and it was inedible. The fish just tasted like salt. Also, everything is soooo overpriced. Would not recommend
Really good food, great service! Unique dishes and nice portion sizes. Will be eating here often.

When I went to Texas Roadhouse in Ithaca on February 1 st, 2020, I was very pleased. They were super busy but the wait wasn't too long and all the staff were very friendly. The food was excellent and our host who seated us and our waitress were very good and helpful.
Amazing restaurant. Very friendly staff and servers. Impeccable service!!

The food is out of this world and the people there are really friendly. The prices are reasonable and the atmosphere is precisely what I expected. You get infinite bread and butter which is warm and buttery. They are a christian, patriotic, company that supports our veterans and emergency responders, and again, the food is awesome. Definitely come here if you can!
The server was awesome he did a great job his name is Steve, the food is great the experience in all was great!!

Great steaks, excellent service, jumbo margherita! What more can you ask for! We had the prime rib and it was one of the best we have had in a long time! Packed, noisy, fun, and lots of peanuts! Go have a good time!

Such a lovely atmosphere! Sitting by the small canal was the best. It's great that this place is also dog-friendly. I couldn't help but feel that the portion is a little small. And it's a pity that they only have normal coffee (no latte and all kinds of options). Anyway, the service was moderately good and I love the ambiance here, including its indoor decoration. Although the food isn't the best I've had in Ithaca, I'd love to come back to be in this atmosphere.

Food was fair at best. We asked for our food to be very well done & it wasn't. The bill wasn't itemized, so we thought we were being overcharged, but we weren't. It needs a good cleaning - cobwebs everywhere & dust. Water stains on some of the pictures makes you wonder if there has been some kind of water damage in the building. The propane heater & propane tank in the dining room were a nice addition, not! When the front/dining area looks like this, makes you wonder what the back/kitchen looks like!!!
Awesome breakfast and Bloody Mary!  All four dishes were great.  Definitely recommend compared to a downtown place with a 45min wait. Well worth the 5 min drive.
Kelly has always done a great job! Delicious food, and reasonable drinks. One of the best parts of Ithaca's history!
The staff here are helpful and prompt plus the patio in the rear of the building is a quest place to have brunch.

We had a great experience here. Not so much because of the food, though that was quite tasty, but because of the lovely server who waited on us and was so compassionate to comp the whole meal for the four of us because she noticed my friend in distress over some sad news of a death in her family. She brought napkins for her tears and brought us an empty check and wrote that she hopes things get better. We were blown away by her kindness and the kindness of the restaurant. We truly were amazed. Thank you for restoring my faith in the world. Bless you.

From the first bite of chive mash potatoes, my toes dance inside my sneakers like a little girl dancing with joy after tasting the sweet taste of a tiny piece of chocolate. It's warm, smooth, and nostalgic. Taste like the mashed potatoes I made with my family when I was a child.

The inside of burger bun has been crispily grilled. Normally I'm not a big fan of blue cheese. But this time, the blue cheese goes very well with the lamb patty, picked shallots, fresh arugula, and light homemade pesto. It's PERFECT. I didn't need to use the ketchup, salt, or pepper at all. This dish's taste is well-balanced with a variety of texture and taste. Since both blue cheese and picked shallots have strong taste, the rest of the ingredients have mild taste. The whole meal feels very hearty and fresh. 

This meal easily found its place in my personal list of favourite burgers!

Ps. The non-alcoholic house cooler that I ordered (Ginger-lavender lemonade) came late (when I already finished half of my burger). But the waitress is very attentive. She came to tell me before the burger arrived that the drink was going to be late because they had to make it from scratch this time. I appreciate that they didn't compromise on food quality and make sure their customer understand. In the end, the taste wasn't to my liking but it was an interesting taste!

Insanely slow service at brunch, was served a cold eggs Benedict after waiting 45 minutes for it to be made. Didn't serve everyone at the table at the same time and I was finished with my meal by the time the last person at the table was served. Awful experience, only thing they are competent at is pouring beers.

Edit: included a 20% gratuity fee on the check as well, pretty ridiculous. Can assure you I will never eat here ever again. Piss poor quality.

Best bar in Ithaca. So many great memories. I know it is going away soon but hopefully it will be reborn stronger in a new location close by on College Ave. Rullies will always be my favorite bar in Ithaca.

My favorite bar in collegetown.  Old school wooden bar, decent craft beer selection. Food is mostly good, always decent.  Event space downstairs.  Ruloff was the last man hand for mass murder in New York.  Last words: hurry up I want to be in hell for dinner.

Friendly staff, great place :) perfect for   birthday parties or other group celebrations. Decent food and a good beverage selection. The rooms have also been clean when I’ve been there. I wish they would expand their song selection to more up to date stuff.

I had no expectations other than knowing it was a karaoke bar. the food was fantastic and I can't wait to go back and try some of the different kinds of french fry concoctions they have. The dumplings were also quite good.

I happen to go when there was a soju tasting and it was very fun to watch and listen to the people doing it. the host of lead them and drinking games and told them history and culture about Korean dining and drinking. It looks like it would be very fun to do when you have a cool group of people.

Overall, fantastic, good food, a fun atmosphere, and fast service.

K-House is a great venue for any celebration, large or small. The owner, Alina is not only accommodating, but kind, fun and professional. The song selection is spot on and the props available to play with are awesome. I've celebrated a couple birthdays here and it's always a blast!!
Had a blast! The people were friendly and the food was amazing..My daughter and I had a great time singing karaoke! Will definitely go back with friends❣️

I would give negative stars if I could for nonchalantly falsely charging people. Was charged for 12 people for 2 hours each, when we explicitly told the employee that several people out of the party left after 1 hour, employee seemed incapable of comprehending, also we were explicitly told via text just a few weeks before the reservation that if we had a party greater than 11 people that the price would be $6/person/hour but they did not honor that, generally good service but incompetent with charging.

FINALLY!  A good pizza in Ithaca.  Listen up all, I almost gave up in Ithaca pizza and wings.  I was convinced that this town just didn’t know how to make a good pizza, and that the only wings available were those terrible gummy ones.  Then, after passing by Northeast Pizza and Beer Co for two years, I finally stopped in.  AMAZING.  Unlike almost every other pizza in Ithaca, this pizza had the ideal amount of sauce and cheese. The toppings were also excellent.  The wings were exactly what I’ve been searching for, crispy without being burnt.  Also a quality sauce on top.  The seasoned fries were also phenomenal.  I will be ranting and raving about this amazing restaurant to everyone I know.  And by the way, their home brewed beer was also phenomenal.  If you’ve given up on Ithaca pizza, I promise that there’s hope.  Northeast Pizza and Beer co has the only good pizza and wings in this town.  And I’m confident in that conclusion.  I will be back frequently.
Good people, great food, delicious beer, enough said.

Always excellent. Freshest pizza in town. Fast like from the oven to the table. But order a personal...the best. This one is a Popeye ( spinach and feta) and sorry but I already ate half lol 😉 my favorite.yummy.

We go for the pizza and wings which are good. I’d rate the pizza and wings a solid three.

My rating is going to be based on service and once the server I review is no longer working there, I will delete my review. We frequent Northeast about once every other week for the last four years and are fairly regular customers.

Our server was the worst I’ve ever had. She came to take our order and repeated it several times, once leaving a part off so I asked if she had it correct and she repeated it again, then again. She then came back again to confirm what our order was. She brought my husbands drink and my son’s and asked again what my drink order was. The pizza order for the table next to us was wrong and she didn’t offer to have a new one made or take it off their bill. They were a family with young children and the mom finally had to go up to the bar to pay their tab. She disappeared for ten minutes during service and the bar tender had to manage tables. After the one family had to pay at the bar, three other tables went to the bar to pay because she didn’t take their tab to them. The family next to us left ten minutes after we sat down and their dirty dishes were still sitting there when we left (which was about an hour later). She had to ask the bartender three times what food belonged to what tables... The service was just terrible. So I’d recommend their food but the next time we go, if the same server is waiting tables we will turn around and go somewhere else.

Disappointed with pizza and wings tonight. Pizza was overcooked, way too salty, with too much crust. They put peppers on wrong half, even after repeating order back correctly. Wings were overcooked, dry and chewy. Were supposed to be garlic parmesan, but didnt have any garlic sticking to them and had hard shredded gobby cheese. This was always our favorite pizza place, but this time had poor quality food that cost too much!

It was my first time ever at chili’s right after I had my heart broken. Our waiter was so kind and the other staff made sure we had everything we ordered. I had the shrimp tacos which were nice and my friends loved the chips that they got as their appetizer. I would definitely come back, since it filled me up for a nice price.

We ordered food to go. They were 17 minutes late bringing our food out to us.  We then waited 4 more minutes for 6 tiny pieces of shrimp that they charged $3 for that was cold.  We got home and ate. The food was bland and cold. We ordered a molten cake. The fudge center was a cold blob.  I guess they didn't even warm that up.  We will wait an extra hour next time and order from texas roadhouse instead. We will not be back.

For locals who know Dinosaur BBQ, you can appreciate it when I say the ribs are on par. Everything we had tasted great. Everyone was friendly and the restaurant and bathrooms were clean. My only complaint was the server. Perhaps he was new. But he was slow, a bit confused, forgot several things, and it wasn't busy. But everyone has an occasional bad day, so I give him the benefit of the doubt. I highly recommend this Chili's. Enjoy!
I always have a great time. The servers are always attentive & pleasant.
Bean and veggie fajitas were great! Good service.

One Quality restaurant in town, good services or waiters. Every week there a new special menu available that create by chef. I will call it Mix cultures restaurant because they sell Japanese sushi, Indian foods, thai foods and some others cultures foods.

Cold food, an over extended junior waiter, and a total lack of professionalism from the manager made for a waste of a lot of money during a night out with the family.  

Four of us ordered about 12 small plates. Of the  first three that came out, 2 were cold and the rice was barely warm. We sent them back. 15 minutes later they come back out, and were just warm.  

Of the several other plates we ordered, the pork buns and pork belly plates were warm but you couldn’t even bite thru the pork belly it was so tough.  3 of the other plates were also just cold, but due to the lack of a waiter that was trying to serve about 40 other people by himself he never came back. 

We honestly had decent food but it was cold, except for the pork dishes.  When we spoke to the manager she said she’d give us free dessert and really didn’t seem to care about what had happened.  Let’s see, all of your food I got already had issues, so you want to give me more, lol.  Eventually she took 3 dishes off the bill.  Thinking back we should have just left after the cold food issue on the first 3 dishes. 

Word to the wise, if they are busy, go somewhere else and definitely don’t sit upstairs.
Food was excellent. Various dishes had very different spices and sauce.  Mushroom small plate was quite tasty.  Seemed very unsalted compared to many Asian restaurants.
Great little Asian fusion place. Very hip and comfortable. Absolutely loved my dish. Great vegan options and even dessert
We shared 5 small plates and loved it! Perfect tapas portions for sampling as much of their amazing menu as possible!
Great Music!! Especially Wednesday Nights.  Amazing Drink specials too especially the featured Fishbowl.

Terrible dj playing music way too loud, even for a nightclub. Strobe lights were obnoxious, and some guy who worked there started telling at me and my friends for apparently trying to close a pair of silk curtains by a window in the isolated corner of the place. The furniture is pretty dodgy, and there is no AC or ventilation down there at all, so consider popping upstairs to cool off and get some fresh air.     I'm sure there are better options around collegetown than this place. I can't really speak for the service or drinks, since it was a Cornell hosted event for summer college, they just had soda. If you do go and feel a bit overwhelmed, try going to the back room and turn down the music in that portion of the place.

A group of my girlfriends and I went here for a bachelorette party on a Thursday night. Based on the reviews we were expecting a great time and atmosphere but we left after 5 minutes of being there. I'm giving 2 stars because I'm thinking it being a Thursday night had something to do with it and all of the employees we spoke with/interacted with were great. When we went the "entertainment" was this one guy randomly playing a guitar with psychadelic music and some sort of video/power point in the background, it was just strange and not at all what we were expecting or hoping for a fun night out. It felt more like we should have been at a grateful dead or Motown concert based on the music and crowd.
Got hit by another patron in the bar, security told me they had never seen me before... I just left. Won’t feel unsafe in a bar.
Typical college bar, and cheap drinks; however, I didn’t think that the DJ was that good. It’s a good spot for college students, but not if you are a grad.

Good option for a drink on the Commons. Good crowd, sit at the bar for best results. Shout-out to bartender Libby for her service!

If you're into dancing, they've got a dance floor and DJs certain nights.

I'll be back.
Amazing bartenders. Super clean. Tons of fun.
Good beers on tap now at time of writing. Not into crowds so we go early. Good place, good staff.
Great songs on jukebox, DJ is lit AF

Great place - large selection of beers, custom cocktails
Karaoke Every Tuesday, DJs Thursday - Friday - Saturday

Food was delicious. Would have given 5 stars but was rather annoyed with the happy hour.  I went there with a couple of friends. We were there at 4:30 and the only people there until after 5. We sat at the bar and had a drink. A little before 5 we were seated. The waitress asked us where we would like to sit, and we said whatever is easiest for you. We sat in the same room as the bar. Once seated I ordered another drink. When I got the bill the drink was not the happy hour price. The waitress said we had to be seated at the bar for happy hour price. It might be helpful to have a sign just to let people know that they need to be at the bar...only five seats though. Other than that I really enjoyed the food and atmosphere.

Dont get me wrong the food and the authenticity was top notch. The prices were reasonable. However the tables were close together and I kept getting bumped into. Also we were put in between two other couples and had no actual privacy. The waitress although nice didnt explain the menu very well and seem to forget about us at times. Overall it was good food but nothing I would go out of the way for.

Liked the tacos. Quac was good. We had chicken tacos, steak tacos. Lamb tacos and shrimp tacos. All were good. Came with 4 I think house made accoumpaiants. Pickled onions, jalapenos, salsa verde and red salsa. Fried plantains were good and something different. Side salad had a dressing on it that was different but good.  Restaurant is downstairs in a basement. Staff was friendly. Place was clean.
Food was delicious as usual. The restaurant is adapting to the state’s guidelines for the space and occupancy. Service was prompt and hygienic.
Over priced. Food was meh. Wont return. Heard great reviews, definitely didnt live up to the hype.

What an amazing place. The bar has such a fine selection of liquors that you will never see at any other bar in Ithaca or really anywhere else within a 100 mile radius. It was really a treat to be able to go in and taste a variety of excellent rums. I would totally recommend this bar for something off the beaten path   10/10.

James Dean, the owner not the actor, has another great place to add to the many he has partnered to open. He created a place for those of us who appreciate great cocktails, craft beers, and good conversation. 

A group of my friends and I have been fans of James’ work for years, and so we are excited that he opened this new place near the west side of the commons. (Also nearby and delicious are Lucky Hare and Watershed.)

I hope you enjoy this place as much as I do. 

Jess

Very nice bar. A good place for young to middle aged folks to grab a drink in Ithaca, a place where bars are typically oriented towards college folks, this is a place where you can grab a high quality and unpretentious cocktail.

Excellent local bar serving up inventive cocktails and a good selection of craft beer, on tap and in cans/bottles. The proprietor is a longtime fixture in the Ithaca bar scene. He's extremely knowledgeable and is always ready with interesting drinks and good conversation.

Jan 10, 2020
Went with high expectation and respect for the place given the recommendation from a friend who knows the owner from liquid state. Would have liked to have an experience like the rest are describing here.  Unfortunately for me, however, the Owner that everyone seems to revere is somewhat of a pretentious pucker to people who have yet come to understand the art and technicality of whisky cocktails and or how to choose. They have a vast collection of bourbons, whisky, scotch and more I am sure. So how does one choose from the diversity?

New to this experience, I kindly asked the bartender that I was looking for a floral whisky on the sweeter side to sip on.  He seems bothered by the fact that I am asking for a recommendation.  He begrudgingly points to six different bottles (which isn't really a recommendation when you aren't describing the drinks themselves).  Having to make a blind decision, on his expansive description of the drinks /s, I think about which to choose.

At this point he has become agitated and RUDELY asks if I am ever going to ever order anything, which is awkward because the lady working beside him was already in the works of making me the whisky sour I had ordered before I even spoke to him. His regulars/friends sitting at the bar even proceed to mock me among themselves.

I have NEVER felt so belittled, so RIDICULED for trying to learn and purchase a good from an establishment that Dean, the owner describes the establishment as a place for, "Getting people to try little things that open up their palates and then they want to come back and try that again.”themselves.  This place clearly only caters to those that understand the process.  His keenness to customer service blows my mind.  I didn't even know they had a menu! Not even a suggestion if I'd like to see it. Regardless, perhaps even uniquely on this night, there was no room for kindness or patience for me.    He pours my chilled whisky as he bellows under his breath, "your whiskey CHILLED," as if to throw the last verbal blow before finally having to end our interaction.  At this point I am feeling quite attacked, isolated and unwelcome that I casually and gracefully extend my middle finger to the bartender.  He proceeds to ask me to leave and grabs the drink from my hands.  I leave without protest relieved I no longer have to endure such a hostile and unwelcoming environment. 

Indeed, this place has earned its name wholeheartedly.  "Nowhere special," hostile, unfriendly, demeaning and a place where social gatekeepers can sip on their egos.

Feel free to respond here Mr. bartender. I'd love to hear how you felt it was appropriate to treat me the way you did.

Wow! So impressed with this place. Loved the Gnocci with the yummy house made lemon cheese. The service here is incredible. They are well staffed, attentive, friendly, and knowledgeable. Loved it so much we came back twice in one night. Perfect place to grab dinner and a drink before seeing a show across the street!
I finally got my Rook hoodie! Love, Love, Love it! Had the duck fat fried chicken again, never disappoints. 🍗❤ service is as always, top notch with this crew.

I've been at least three times, and have yet to be disappointed in the slightest.
Such a great selection of dishes prepared for very well.  Really like that you can get a burger and fries if you want too, which is delicious.
Has an awesome feel, of a modern city place, while being very accessible.
Service is also excellent.
The drinks and the food are great. The fried chicken and collard greens are fantastic. The service is quick and attentive as well. Definitely a great place for a night out.

Solid eats. As the other reviewers have said it is a little pricey but you are getting awesome food and I don't mind paying a little more. When I go away for a week or weekend I just don't hold back, if there is something new, unique and fun, I want to try it. I personally didn't think the prices were out of control I think they were quite all right. I have paid more money for really subpar food before, and all of the food here is aces.  Our server was awesome. Their beer list is equally awesome, You can find some beers here but you won't find elsewhere. A good amount of German, and some Polish beer as well. I think I would call this comfort food, it feels like gastro pub? We started with some gandalfini fries. They were terrific, a lot of flavor there, executed nicely.  I got the fried chicken and greens. Do it. As the others have said you won't regret it. She got the pancetta (absolutely five star) with some fingerling potatoes.  For dessert we got the donuts of the day which were absolutely stellar. I believe they had an Earl Gray glaze or reduction and the texture was more like crumb cake, dynamite .it wasn't overly sweet which would have ruined it IMO.  Now for the constructive criticism... And I didn't feel like it warranted taking a half a point or a point off. I firmly believe that the music sets the feel, tone and mood. The bluegrass style lively music made me want to drink up and laugh. There was some music that was really really slow dark and down the place was a little bit empty at first so it was kind of droning. Kind of like Radiohead but more sad. I like the upbeat bluegrass stuff though, it fits the feel and style more of the place. Without a doubt 100% I will be coming back to eat and drink here again. I really wish my hometown had more places like this.

The restaurant is a nice hidden area in the Marriott hotel, the food was good and I especially recommend their ‘little bites’ menu which offers pulled pork blt sandwiches and grilled cheese with soup, it was a great intermittent meal whilst waiting out the rain. Their dessert selection was also great, I recommend the Creme brûlée.

The drinks are good (I tried 18 karat cocktail and it was delicious). The food appeared to be more on a salty side for my taste, especially the pesto fries. But overall it’s a nice restaurant with a good vibe.
I had my breakfast there. I ordered egg Benedict, It was not good at all. I ate it because I was supper hungry. It is not worth the price. However, their coffee is Great. I do not recommend it .

Waited 15 minutes, no server showed up. Had a reservation and was sat immediately upon arrival. Host offered to get drinks, which never arrived. At about 8 minutes with no service, got attention of manager  who said he would get our server. No one arrived.  They seemed too focused on setting up for a couple of larger parties coming in soon than the customers already there.

The customer service at this hotel restaurant is excellent. Our server, Jewel, was very patient with my son as he ordered things that were off the menu. This made the experience pleasant for everyone.
The Belgian waffle with the warm compote was great. Even the breakfast buffet was worth it. The fresh fruit was sweet and the assorted of pastries were great too. We would eat there again, even if we were not at this hotel.

result.name: Finger Lakes Cajun Seafood & Hot Pot

reviews.text: It was my first time at this place and it definitely makes me want to come back for more. I had the spicy hot pot which tasted great. My friend enjoyed the seafood boil as well. The staff was accomdating and the place was clean.
Hands down the best hotpot place in Ithaca! Beats all the overpriced restaurants in collegetown. Great service and a good selection of food and sauces.

They're pretty new and are a little off the beaten path so they have some kinks to iron out, mostly with the consistency of their brand/name, but the staff are all so nice and helpful! The food was tasty, love the sauce bar, all the ingredients were fresh and appealing. Big screens of pop music videos and a party room signify a willingness to accommodate big groups. Will definitely make this a regular stop!

We were double charged and when we asked them to fix it they were arguing with us. But when they finally agreed that the mistake was in their part they took out to go box with food and there it away. We had great experience the first time we went. Not the second time.

reviews.author_name: Elmira NY First Church of the Nazarene
reviews.text: Not a buffet. We ordered from the menu what we wanted in our pot. Then you cook it yourself at your table. It's an experience not all you can gobble down and leave.

I've been going to their Sunday breakfast/brunch buffet as a special treat for years now. There's nothing else like it in Ithaca. The buffet has standard breakfast fare but a couple surprises like Eggs Benedict. The highlights are fresh made Belgian waffles and omelettes prepared in the dining area.

Visited Home show. Won a Keurig coffee machine. Thanks Laman Real Estate. 
Denny
On Sundays they have a very very very good breakfast buffet and turkey dinner
We have our Sunday breakfast here faithfully every Sunday... If you've ever been , go. Then you will understand. By far the best homemade waffle ever!!
Great buffet

Great bookstore and cafe.  I love to go there when I have free time. Although I do not purchase books regularly,  I still eat at the cafe while reading a book, without buying it. Good membership deals,  ten percent discount on everything for twenty five dollars each year, and it is well worth it  if you spend  251 dollars there. Staff are kind and pleasant,  and parking is really available. Will recommend.
Love the atmosphere and the little cafe inside. The food there taste very good yes mm I eat very cool. Helpful staff and a wide variety of books and games.

Went I went to a Barnes & Nobles outside of Philadelphia with a good friend of mine. We were looking at children's book since we both babysit for younger kids and were both high school students. But my friend and I were sitting down and reading them and employees were walking by laughing at us for reading children books. Like what the hell I'm reading them to make sure that they are books that the kids haven't read before and your just sitting there laughing at us for reading them. Like learn to mind your own business and don't  laugh at people for wanting to read children's books even though they may be adults.

I was picking out some books for my grandchildren. A daunting task. The staff here were very helpful, especially the young lady with the colorful hair. She helped me pick out a couple teen books, and helped me find the sequel to "Lionheart", a great book about Richard I . All in all, a positive experience, that Amazon cannot match...personal service.
I love this place, nice atmosphere, great selection of items and friendly customer service
Some very good bargains, some stuff just cheap. Items always changing, you never know what you'll find. Recently purchased full sized mattress/boxed springs set for under $300.

They don’t have everything but what they do have is offered at major savings. I found brand name products that were priced at less than half of what I pay at other places. They have a nice book section as well with books you’d actually want to read.
Always somthing new to find at this store so you never know what you will find ....good stuf cheap
There are some good deals. Staff is always helpful.
I found what I was looking for. Good deals. Nice music. Nice employee at register

The service at this location was great. The food was done fast and everything was clean. My issues were more with the food which I know isn't controlled by the specific location. The "signature" hot chocolate just tasted like powder in water, nothing special. I got a breakfast wrap, but there was like 1 scrambled egg and 1 piece of bacon that was overshadowed by the giant wrap
The baker there is amazing.

NEVER ORDER!!!! delivery from this Panera. They will take 3 hours to deliver a meal that should realistically take 40-45mins to come. I was able to view where my driver was driving and watched him go to the opposite part of town before coming to my home. Food was cold when arrived.

Dude,  don't come here after 9 apparently they close at 10 so they run out of stuff by 9. I got a Caesar salad with no romaine lettuce in it "Amazing" not so much... I didn't get a baguet piece or any bread because they're all out... why cook more right?? I mean we close in an hour. Not to happy with my  $42 purchase of leftovers.
I wish they did not put cinnamon in the soup.

We did not have such a great experience this past weekend. I ordered the French toast and it was very dry, almost as if they did not soak it long enough in the egg mixture. For what I received I feel it was overpriced. I’m willing to pay for a good meal and unfortunately I did not receive a good meal. The coffee was very good though. Our server never introduced himself, and he did not seem too motivated. Perhaps it was knowing he was getting a guaranteed 18% gratuity, whether it was earned or not.  We probably won’t be back, because of the gratuity and what I feel is overpriced menu. It’s a shame because it is a nice place and have great coffee.
Great place! There can be quite a wait on the weekend, but definitely worth the time spent. Highly recommend visiting before it closes.
Delicious food. Be prepared to wait, and it's on the expensive side. The waitress could've been a little more welcoming... But overall we had a great brunch here.
A really cute and fun place for brunch. Try to get in early though, as it's always busy

Saw a friend here.  It was quite uncomfortable seating otherwise okay.  Pretty good sound and close quarters when moving around room.  If that is what people want when they are promoting a new CD, it is okay.  I've heard the food is quite good.  I haven't tasted yet.

I arrived hungry an a moderately busy Sunday. It took 35 minutes for two sandwiches to be made. I watched the two staffers who were making them spend more time chatting and moving around than cooking. The food was decent, but it would benefit anyone to order ahead of time. There’s no sense of urgency here.

Very kind and nice staff. The range of sandwiches they offer is huge and the cashiers do a good job if you have questions. The range of pastries is incredible and very tempting! Never tried but they do have a morning buffet breakfast that has all the essential breakfast items. 
I really like the coffee and the espresso drinks! One of the best places after gimme coffee to get coffee from!
Really good food and great staff. You can get a good meal here and some minor groceries and deli/bakery goods to purchase. If I live out in Ithaca I would frequent this place more often.

We love this bakery! I grew-up in the greater Ithaca area, and a family emergency brought me back with my niece. We stopped for some treats to share; as an eleven year old, she loved the staff and all the treats.

We absolutely loved this Bakery! Was an amazing find. Everything was so wonderful. Staff was attentive and helpful. Great little atmosphere. You can tell this is a very popular place with locals Travelers and college students alike. We were especially pleased with the vegetarian and vegan options! Everything was amazing

Everytime I go there the staff is out smoking and they can NEVER get my coffee right. I dont know why I even still go there. I think I'm goung to have to find somewhere else to get coffee. If i could give zero stars I would. Plus they are ALWAYS out of something. Weather it's cups or whatever. They don't plan accordingly.. Something needs to be done with this location.
Love that this place is so convenient to where I work. I love the veggie egg white sandwich on a English muffin.

Don't make the mistake of ordering inside, I've never waited so long for the three people in line ahead of me. And I wish I could say that was a one-off experience but both times I've been to this branch have been upwards of 20 minutes, just to order, *with only three people ahead of me*. 

The staff look like they're focused entirely on the drive thru (which seemed like it was moving at a normal pace) and if I weren't on foot that day, it would have made much more sense to stay in my car. Which is a shame, though I realize I'm probably in the minority on this.
Horrible. So slow. It's called fast food for a reason.

We love Dunkin’ Donuts, however this could be the nicest and slowest one we’ve been to. 15 minutes in the drive thru with only 4 cars a head of us. I almost wanted to check for a pulse on the guy at the window

These guys came highly recommended however I've never really made a point to stop in until I had to use the bathroom so bad. I asked for decaf and she offered it in a latte (never had one before figured what the heck I didn't even want the coffee) she was SO pleasant even had dairy free options! ...but when I tasted that latte.. Drank it right down, couldn't stop! I AM SOLD!! This is my new favorite place!!  Cheers 😎👍
Phenomenal coffee. The hot chocolate is the best I've ever had. Local atmosphere. Well worth a visit!

First time here and was greeted with smiles. Makes you feel welcomed. Barista was super nice. He took the time to explain the difference between the two coffee flavors they had at the time. The croissants were flaky and delicious. Will be back the next time we're in Cornell.
The standard. What every coffee shop should aspire to be. Impeccable staff, great roasts, short lines and cool stuff.
One of the few coffee shops on the area that knows how to properly prepare espresso.

So many places serve the same, dry, sugary waffles you can get at any fast food restaurant. Really impressed with these handmade works of art. Friendly service, nice amount of room to sit. They also have sandwiches and excellent coffee.

A fantastic breakfast of 2 eggs, salty bacon and a sweet waffle grilled to perfection topped off with a side of banana and a yummy Latte. Done fast, done right. Only negative was the lack of a change table in the somewhat grotty unisex upstairs bathroom and no sign indicating that there was a change table in the downstairs bathroom.

Always go for the cornbread waffle if you like savory! The grilled cheese sandwiches and tomato soup are also excellent. Wish the coffee was a little better, but sometimes you have to prioritize and the priority here is the food I think.

The signature chicken and waffle was great. Crispy chicken over a light fluffy waffle. However, the cafe is serve yourself, the tables are not regularly bussed, and this does not help with the price. My friend ordered a waffle with bananas and syrup - They upcharged her for both additions and what came out was a tiny cup of syrup and a half banana just placed on top of the waffle. Not worth the money!

This beautiful spot was nothing less than an absolute delight to visit. There are a few aspects of life that make it as rich and beautiful and glorious as it can be in its little joys, and I’d have to say a waffle café is really high up there on that list. There are a myriad of options, graciously including gluten free options, and framed quotes of Leslie Knope, if my memory informs me correctly, all of which must tell you that this glorious establishment is worth a visit. Or ten. You do you.

We used the kiosk for our order figuring that it would be faster! Nope it took 25 minutes for our food,then it wasn't all there! Plus the restaurant was just plain dirty! Top top it off their shake machine was down!
Great, fresh coffee and very accommodating and friendly staff!
It's McDonald's. You know exactly what you're getting every time. This location is very convenient, clean and well-kept with very friendly staff.
The food is always fresh and hot! The staff are always very nice to me! The only thing they need to do is keep it a little more cleaner near the drink station because people are dirty sadly!

Automatic one star for the self-serve kiosks malfunctioning and being cash only, forcing me to waste several minutes at the kiosk only to have to wait in line to get up to the counter anyway.  Place was also way too busy and not as well-equipped to deal with it as they should have been, with outrageously long wait times (for a McDonald's) both inside and at the drive through.  Unacceptable, and I won't be back unless they fix these issues.

result.name: Chatty Cathy Coffee and Juice Co.

reviews.text: Pleasant atmosphere! Make your own yogurts and juices. Peaceful study spot. Clean. Nice staff.
Amazing smoothies! Staff is so friendly and knowledgeable

Honestly, the sweetest baristas in the world! Very understanding and outgoing, could strike up a conversation about anything lol! The owners of the establishment are also very cool and very friendly people! Best açaí ever, no doubt. Overall this lil cafe is perfect
Today was my first day here I loved the acai bowl will be coming soon

Came there expecting it to be a little better then average but i can say it was awesome! Ordered oatmeal expecting to get a little portion but hot dang i left full. Let's have some real talk though the lady on the logo is Linda from Bob's burgers. (Look it up for real)
Loveliest outdoor seating and they respect the ADA laws

Will not go back.  They told us over the phone no reservations then after getting there and waiting an hour they told us tables were reserved.  It’s just a red neck bar for locals.  Don’t waste your time.
I like the bubbles and serving sizes. The bubbles are not too soft and actually have flavor which is good. The environment is nice and so are the staff.
Kung Fu Tea has a great variety of options that allows every person in a group to get something they like. Compared to the other bubble tea places in collegetown, this one has more sweet teas.

Always fast and good. I love getting their brown sugar Ginger tea when my throat is feeling sick, always makes me feel better. I prefer their bubbles to most other brands since their bubbles are never too chewy and have their own flavor.
Pretty good selection of drinks, even if bubble tea isn't really my thing.  Quick, friendly service, although the prices are quite high.

The bubble tea is consistently very good. They have all the options you would expect from a Kung Fu Tea, and you can customize sugar and ice levels to your liking. I recommend a Thai Milk tea, especially if you like Thai iced tea.  Unfortunately, they have a $7 credit/debit card minimum so if you don’t have cash, go with a friend or get two teas and save one for later.

One of the very few food options within the Cornell University campus. You'll get mostly deli-type food, which was okay and filling enough, but nothing to write home about. The place is inside the same building as the university bookstore/gift shop.
Sandwiches is good. Staff are friendly.

Went here for a quick lunch while visiting the Cornell campus and I was really quite pleased. I got the tofu bahn mi and it was delightful! Just a well constructed and good-tasting sandwich. Comes with a salad, which is tricky to eat on the go. The actual dining area is small so it's usually VERY crowded, your best bet is to grab something and go like I did, even if that means it will be a tad colder. Pretty quick service and conveniently located right in the Cornell store.

Excellent food! I'm back in town for my 35th reunion.  We stopped here for a quick bite. Nice menu. Great food. I had the chicken milano and my wife had the beef brisket. Nice selection of sides as well.  Only limited seating available.
Best coffee on campus, except Gimme. The staff members are very friendly.

The crab and corn soup is soooooo tasty! Try it. 
Layout of the food area is a bit odd which creates a bad logistical flow for people getting food and those exiting with their food. Also, the staff are seemingly unfriendly and I swear I thought the guy serving in the hot food section was going to drip sweat into the curry. The older lady next to him served the rice so sloppy. The dish looked ugly because of how it was served and presented and so I left it. But, the crab and corn soup is fantastic!
Very polite and nice staff. The food is good and the ingredients are fresh. Can't really remember a negative thing about the cafe from the few times I have stopped by to grab lunch or coffee.

Great central location.
With a good vibe atmosphere.
Not a lot of choices, decent sandwiches and wraps!
Friendly staff.
Great service and convenient location-- right in Duffield hall on campus.  Can get busy at lunch time.  They have hot items and cold grab and go stuff.
The people working here have absolutely no idea about gastronomy. Abstain from this place if you are someone of good taste.

Mattin's Cafe is convenient but not cheap.  They have a decent selection of wraps and other refrigerated fast food.  Their chocolate muffins are addicting, and for this reason I would recommend staying away from them!  Their prepared foods can be pretty decent, but their calzones are from the freezer and cost almost as much as freshly made calzones from DP Dough.

Had the pleasure of ordering from Jackie a few days ago. She went above and beyond in my order during a very stressful time. The food was great and the customer service was even greater. Will definitely come back again!
Good food, good choices, excellent and friendly staff. Try the chipotle chicken wrap. Good for hot food or something quick. No espressos though.
The good here is really good, very healthy options. Very different from the University run food choices on campus.
They have coffee from Gimme Coffee, which is quite good. Everything else is unremarkable.

Food is simple, which allows the good quality, local ingredients to stand out. Soup is filling and comforting, but menu changes daily so you don't always know what you will get. Pastries and coffee are also quality as a snack!
The only place on campus that makes their own soups daily. Great service and great taste.
They have a great tea selection, and I always enjoy getting a donut or croissant from them too.
Good meal w friends
Service is super slow.  Don't waste your time
They play lit music

Located on the Cornell University campus, The big red Barn is a wonderful meeting place for graduate students and exhibits. The parking lot offers a stunning view of Cornell's watchtower and landscape. Indoors is a cafe and plenty of room to stretch out with tables and chairs sofas and nooks here and there to settle in or visit friends. Housed in a renovated Barn the building has an old-time ambience that is accentuated with some new architecture that blends with the building seamlessly. The building is surrounded by lovely gardens.

EXTREMELY rude to my group and I as soon as we walked in the door. I do not frequent this place often, however I decided to go for a lunch break with some colleagues, and the cashier had an attitude with me about the order in which I paid for my food. She then came over to our table on her lunch break to yell at one of my colleagues to move her chair over. She wasn’t even on the clock anymore! THEN the manager came over and accused us of drinking alcohol and said that we loudly stated “We are drinking alcohol at the barn” so she was forced to intervene, which is just not a real thing someone would say normally. They targeted us for no reason. They need to do some more training. Beyond unprofessional.

Great meeting place for grad students during their happy hour specials on Friday afternoons. Hard to beat the $1 beers and free finger food. Also, a surprisingly good dance space for the monthly salsa night and semi occasional dance party.

It is the best place for grad students at Cornell. Free coffee from 8 to 11 am, 1 dollar beer in the afternoon, and its quiet and warm. Just a great place for reading and writing in general, especially in the morning
Good place to work, chat, network and have fun
Good food and the staff is very friendly
Good food, but not the cheapest option.
Staff are so helpful and friendly.  Nice to see their smiling faces and jolly dispositions.
The food is good and the eating spot is so open. In the summer it is so bright!

The sandwiches are actually quite good. I like that it is open for a long time so if I miss the usual lunch time and can still grab something to eat. Also there is rarely much of a queue so it is perfect for something fast. The Big Red Barn also has sandwiches but it takes them longer to make them, in my experience. 

The view from the physics building, inside of which Goldie's is situated, if fantastic. Really a pleasure to eat here.
Love their salads they specially make just for you! Great price too.
Healthy salad  food for a reasonable price. Not much to complain about.
Best cafe on Cornell's campus
Avocado Toast with Chicken Noodle Soup. Decent food, tried to overcharge.
Good food and nice place. But they should place their location in an easier place to access
Excellent place. Cute Batistas
Great service and food.
Bueno y bonito espacio para comer algo mientras estudias
The owner is so sweet and makes the some of the best boba/bubble tea in Ithaca. It’s a cozy, quiet space to study until late or meet up with people for long chats

The owner lady is very nice and sweet. She makes you feel welcome and will give you small snacks sometimes. The food is good but can be hit or miss at times. There are a lot of bubble tea flavors but it is not as good as other nearby places
Awesome place. Very good Japanese cuisine taste. The lady here is very nice. Highly recommended. But it might take a while to have food ready.
Awesome place. Awesome flavor. Very authentic Japanese food. Tho a bit slow. But in general, highly recommended.

They make a great mocha and have a variety of treats. Something for everyone. Highly recommended two thumbs up.

The coffee is good and the bakery bread with cheese is fantastic

A moderately nice CTB branch. Beware though: the grilled food smell will stuck to your hair long after you left the place. This branch's strength is that it has less people; thus, not less noisy than other CTBs. Its weakness lies in its limited cake options.
Amazing sandwiches and coffee drinks! Very reasonable prices, too.

This is a very friendly and cozy place right in the middle of Shops at Ithaca. There are lots of small tables and comfortable chairs to sit at, and there's no rush like you might feel at a place like Starbucks. I can sit here and write or draw as long as I'm comfortable! 

Last visit I had a bagel with egg, ham, and cheese - cooked perfectly, bagel wasn't burned, absolutely delicious. If I'm in a rush, I can also stop in for their half-moons, which make for a great treat. Food is priced very well on top of that. I'd definitely recommend checking them out for a great local place!
Warm atmosphere, good coffee and friendly staff. Highly recommend!
I recommended this place to everyone. They give 10% discount for senior, too. That's really nice.
Best coffee at Ithaca mall.  Friendly, caring owner.  Good half Moon cookies.  I like orange best, but there are many, plus scones, sandwiches, soups.
Every time I come here, the experience is delightful. The coffee, the music, the food, the staff, and the comfort is top notch!

I worked here as a waitress for a year, and I cannot recommend it enough, both as an employee AND as a customer. The food is great, the people are great, the atmosphere? Shocker: also great. I am an Ithaca native, and I can promise you that you will not find better breakfast, for a better price, literally anywhere else in town. If you want to get a delicious meal and give your money to deeply good people, this is the spot. Trust me.
Egg-cellent omelettes! ;) cute atmosphere with very tasty food and great service. Staff was attentive and the locally sourced food made a difference!

Had a delicious brunch with friends on a Sunday morning. Staff was fantastic and attentive. Food was excellent and fast. We had a group six and everything was spot on! I ordered the pecan waffle special. This waffle was wonderful...made with browned butter, topped with chantilly cream, toasted pecans, and drizzled with maple syrup! Yummy! Featured in the photos are items that our table ordered: Waffle Special,  Eggs Benedict, and the Omelet Special.  Will definitely return! What a gem. FYI - cash or check only.

Amazing food and good quantity! Loved the Brioche French Toast there, do try it. The only caveat is that it is a cash only place so do carry cash with you before you go there although there is an ATM in the building!

I live right nearby and love their service and locally-sourced food. Food is good, selection nothing too amazing, but just really solid. Free coffee refills are a plus! It's no wonder there's always a huge line during weekends. Staff are friendly, though service is not very fast. Plan for a little extra time to finish up a meal here.

This is the one and only gas station I go to in town. Its member card saves you 10c per gallon and gives you 10% off everything in the convenient store. The savings are great for an Uber driver like me and the discount on snacks for my riders is a bonus.

The staff are truly lazy and very unfriendly. If I wasn't almost out of gas I would have gone else where. The place needs to hire more "customer friendly" people that consider customers to be top priority.

Great gas prices, especially if you become a member. There's always hot food in the carrousel, and ripe bananas. Decent coffee for a gas station.

This is an excellent local Cafe with amazing food and very friendly staff. After ordering, food came out amazingly fast, which with two hungry waiting kids, was appreciated. Excellent soup and sandwiches, and great coffee and Chai. Will be returning here again.

Very cute and inviting building from the outside. Inside was just as cute and the staff could obviously tell that we were new and they were very helpful. The food came out very quickly and my Tex Mex Melt sandwich was fresh and delicious. The flavor pairings complimented each other well. Would definitely recommend this place for it's cozy-cafe atmosphere and its selection of quality food and baked goods.

Nice refreshing place to get a snack or a drink while studying in Olin Library.  The prices aren't too bad and you get a great view of the Arts Quad when you sit by the windows!  The selection isn't too bad!
Best cafe at the apt corner. Easy to access while reading in Olin or Uris. Starbucks, bagels, and other brunch kind eatables are there. Great place for iced mocha and cappuccino. Very friendly staff.
